r-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"3fb9b3c\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-cc88e83\" data-id=\"cc88e83\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8fa06ee elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8fa06ee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Open Abdomen (OA) & Temporary Abdominal Closure (TAC)<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-f8cf19b elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"f8cf19b\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-c41fc39\" data-id=\"c41fc39\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-f0c8a39 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"f0c8a39\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Indications<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Damage Control in an Unstable\/Crashing Patient<\/li><li>Excessive Edema\/Tension &amp; Unable to Close Fascia<ul><li>\u201cThe Difficult Abdomen\u201d<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Abdominal Compartment Syndrome<\/li><li>\u201cSecond-Look\u201d to Reevaluate Questioned Bowel Viability or Hemostasis<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Techniques<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><em>Negative Pressure Wound Therapy (NPWT) <\/em>\u2013 Use of a Negative Pressure System to Assist in Closure<ul><li>Commercial Systems Include AbThera &amp; VAC Therapy<\/li><li>Suctioned at 100-150 mmHg<\/li><li>More Expensive but Provides Excellent Fluid Control<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Vacuum-Pack (Barker\u2019s Technique) <\/em>\u2013 The \u201cHome-Made\u201d NPWT System (\u201cGhetto-VAC\u201d)<ul><li>Technique:<ul><li>A Nonadherent Sheet is Placed Over the Abdominal Viscera Beneath the Anterior &amp; Lateral Abdominal Walls<ul><li>Necessary to Protect the Bowel<\/li><li>Add Intermittent Perforations Through the Sheet to Promote Fluid Absorption<\/li><li>Options: Polyethylene Sheet, \u201c10\/10\u201d Steri-Drape, X-Ray Cassette Cover<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>A Surgical Dressing (Towels\/Sponges) is Placed Over the Sheet<\/li><li>Two Silicone Suction Drains are Placed Along the Dressing to Allow Negative Pressure<\/li><li>An Adhesive Sheet (Ioban) is Covered Over the Wound &amp; Skin Edges<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Suctioned at 100-150 mmHg<\/li><li>Uses Cheap Material Already Found in the OR if Other NPWT Systems are Unavailable<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Patch Closure<\/em> \u2013 Use of a Synthetic Mesh Bridge Between the Fascia (PTFE Mesh or a Wittmann Patch)<ul><li>Can Additionally Use a WVAC Over the Patch<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Bogota Bag<\/em> \u2013 A Sterile IV Fluid Bag is Sutured to Each Side of the Abdominal Wall<\/li><li><em>Zipper Closure<\/em> \u2013 Zipper Device Sutured to Wound Edges to Permit Multiple Repeated Examinations<\/li><li><em>Skin-Only Closure<\/em> \u2013 Uses Staples or Towel Clamps Every 1-2 cm, Covered with a Plastic Drape<\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-3730100\" data-id=\"3730100\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e6e2444 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"e6e2444\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-10215 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Abthera.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"335\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Abthera.jpg 500w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Abthera-300x201.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p><p>ABTHERA WVAC <sup>1<\/sup><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-fca94e9 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"fca94e9\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-11625 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Vacuum-Pack-Barker.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"195\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Vacuum-Pack-Barker.jpg 500w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Vacuum-Pack-Barker-300x117.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p><p>Barker Vacuum-Pack <sup>2<\/sup><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-ebe662d elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"ebe662d\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-01a427b\" data-id=\"01a427b\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a671c94 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"a671c94\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Closure of the Difficult Abdomen (When Primary Closure is Not Possible)<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-97b5aae elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"97b5aae\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-1cf1a35\" data-id=\"1cf1a35\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a1e0fe5 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"a1e0fe5\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Adjuncts<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Appropriate Diuresis<\/li><li>WVAC to Drain Exudate &amp; Decrease Edema<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Options<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><em>Velcro (Hook &amp; Loop)<\/em> \u2013 Two Velcro Sheets Allow Progressive Tightening to Close Over a Period of Time<ul><li><em>Wittmann Patch<\/em> \u2013 Attached to the Fascial Edges<\/li><li><em>Transabdominal Wall Traction (TAWT) Method<\/em> \u2013 Uses a Whittmann Patch Attached to the Underside of the Abdominal Wall, Lateral to the Rectus Muscle with Sutures Brought Through the Skin to a Bolster<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Bogota Bag<\/em> \u2013 A Sterile IV Fluid Bag is Sutured to Each Side of the Abdominal Wall &amp; Progressively Tightended (Similar to a Whittmann Patch)<\/li><li><em>Canica ABRA System<\/em> \u2013 Elastic Bands Trough Each Side Allow Progressive Tightening to Close Over a Period of Time<\/li><li><em>Delayed Skin Grafting<\/em> \u2013 Can Either Place a Temporary\/Absorbable Mesh or Use WVAC to Form Granulation Tissue Prior to Grafting<\/li><li><em>Skin-Only Closure<\/em> \u2013 Allows Recovery of the Acute Period with Plan for Abdominal Wall Reconstruction Later Under More Favorable Terms<\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-1bb820e elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"1bb820e\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-25 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-9bedeef\" data-id=\"9bedeef\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-cf1f4ec elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"cf1f4ec\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-10213 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Wittmann-Patch.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"374\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/Wittmann-Patch.jpg 500w, https:\/\/operativerevie